Prion diseases, or Transmissible Spongiform Encephalopathies (TSEs), are fatal neurodegenerative disorders that include Kuru, Creutzfeldt-Jakob disease (CJD), and Gerstman-Straussler-Scheinker (GSS) syndrome in man. These diseases are associated with the deposition of aggregates of disease-related isoforms (PrPSc) of a host-encoded protein (PrPC) within the central nervous system
